22/04/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The European Commission, the Council of Europe and the OSCE mission made public on Wednesday (21 April) expert recommendations on Croatia's media law and defamation provisions in the criminal code. The three European institutions set up the joint expert team at the government's request. The report urges the cabinet to amend legal provisions on programme content and access to public information. It also recommends transferring defamation provisions from the criminal code to the civil code. (OSCE press release, HINA - 21/04/04)
